WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.001 --> 00:00:02.312
Previously on will Trent…

2
00:00:02.336 --> 00:00:04.105
let's talk about Paul camp a no.

3
00:00:04.129 --> 00:00:05.398
Get off me. trashcan.

4
00:00:05.422 --> 00:00:06.816
You know each other?

5
00:00:06.840 --> 00:00:08.735
Paul and I grew up together
in the children's home.

6
00:00:08.759 --> 00:00:11.029
I can't believe you
guys are still hooking up.

7
00:00:11.053 --> 00:00:13.364
You know there's a whole world
out there full of people. right?

8
00:00:13.388 --> 00:00:16.117
- You have nightmares? Me too.
- Four nights out of seven.

9
00:00:16.141 --> 00:00:17.744
I was gonna kill you.

10
00:00:17.768 --> 00:00:20.288
There is a monster in there after all.

11
00:00:20.312 --> 00:00:22.832
You brought calamity upon our family.

12
00:00:24.858 --> 00:00:27.527
See you soon.

13
00:00:29.029 --> 00:00:30.089
No!

14
00:00:37.746 --> 00:00:39.873
Why are you doing this?

15
00:00:56.348 --> 00:00:57.975
Please. Don't.

16
00:01:08.735 --> 00:01:09.987
Oopsie.

17
00:01:11.321 --> 00:01:14.175
Sorry about that.

18
00:01:26.336 --> 00:01:30.173
The victim. joelle horn baker.
could have escaped. She stopped.

19
00:01:32.009 --> 00:01:33.010
Why?

20
00:01:34.428 --> 00:01:36.430
Death was waiting in
the opposite direction.

21
00:01:45.605 --> 00:01:48.400
The angle of these nails
suggests the killer was much taller.

22
00:01:48.984 --> 00:01:50.378
assumed to be male.

23
00:01:50.402 --> 00:01:53.798
Given the unique choice of weaponry.
he wanted Mrs. Hornbaker to suffer.

24
00:01:53.822 --> 00:01:55.758
No signs of forced entry anywhere.

25
00:01:55.782 --> 00:01:58.118
and it doesn't look like
anything was stolen in the house.

26
00:01:59.870 --> 00:02:01.264
Anyone get a hold of her husband?

27
00:02:01.288 --> 00:02:03.433
Eli horn baker was notified an hour ago.

28
00:02:03.457 --> 00:02:05.584
He's on his way back from
a business trip in Memphis.

29
00:02:07.252 --> 00:02:09.254
The killer knew she was alone.

30
00:02:09.838 --> 00:02:12.174
Mrs. Hornbaker was the
target of this home invasion.

31
00:02:12.924 --> 00:02:13.925
How are we doing there?

32
00:02:14.593 --> 00:02:16.011
I'm not finding anything.

33
00:02:17.095 --> 00:02:20.158
No smudges. no fabric
impressions. nothing?

34
00:02:20.182 --> 00:02:21.242
Not a one.

35
00:02:21.266 --> 00:02:22.267
Well. keep looking.

36
00:02:23.769 --> 00:02:25.246
The killer wiped down the scene.

37
00:02:25.270 --> 00:02:26.831
Nothing we haven't seen before.

38
00:02:26.855 --> 00:02:29.459
But how often do they clean for
prints and leave us the murder weapon

39
00:02:29.483 --> 00:02:30.484
for us to find?

40
00:02:31.068 --> 00:02:32.361
Never.

41
00:02:40.410 --> 00:02:41.828
She reached for this drawer…

42
00:02:43.330 --> 00:02:46.500
To get a knife to defend
herself. a chef's knife.

43
00:02:47.834 --> 00:02:48.895
So where is it?

44
00:02:48.919 --> 00:02:49.961
You collect a knife?

45
00:02:51.046 --> 00:02:52.398
Nope.

46
00:02:52.422 --> 00:02:53.782
Maybe the killer took it with him.

47
00:02:54.466 --> 00:02:57.386
She could have defended
herself and gotten a piece of him.

48
00:02:58.553 --> 00:03:01.848
No. I didn't let her get that close.

49
00:03:02.683 --> 00:03:03.809
You?

50
00:03:05.769 --> 00:03:08.039
- What?
- Excuse me. No. I… let me through.

51
00:03:08.063 --> 00:03:10.625
I live on this street. I
have some information.

52
00:03:10.649 --> 00:03:12.168
- What the hell is this?
- I didn't come to talk

53
00:03:12.192 --> 00:03:13.252
to a schmo in a uniform.

54
00:03:13.276 --> 00:03:16.005
Let me talk to the main guy.
whoever's in charge. Not you.

55
00:03:16.029 --> 00:03:17.090
Paul?

56
00:03:17.114 --> 00:03:19.717
Will. Thank god. See?
This is what I meant.

57
00:03:19.741 --> 00:03:21.177
This is who I talk to.

58
00:03:21.201 --> 00:03:22.553
What the hell are you doing here?

59
00:03:22.577 --> 00:03:24.514
I live down the street. I
moved a couple years ago.

60
00:03:24.538 --> 00:03:27.040
Okay. Remember my partner.
special agent faith Mitchell?

61
00:03:27.541 --> 00:03:30.168
Yeah. hi. Listen. I know who did it.

62
00:03:35.632 --> 00:03:37.318
Paul. this looks like a toddler drew it.

63
00:03:37.342 --> 00:03:40.429
What? It has all the key descriptors.

64
00:03:40.929 --> 00:03:46.244
Big. burly. bag. beard. brunette.
Five bs. Do your job. go find him.

65
00:03:46.268 --> 00:03:47.954
When did you see this individual?

66
00:03:47.978 --> 00:03:49.122
4:00 A.M. this morning.

67
00:03:49.146 --> 00:03:50.665
What were you doing up at 4:00 A.M.?

68
00:03:50.689 --> 00:03:52.708
- 4:00 A.M. club.
- What?

69
00:03:52.732 --> 00:03:55.795
Studies show that people who get
up at 4:00 A.M. are more productive.

70
00:03:55.819 --> 00:03:58.714
maximize their day and live five
years longer than the average person.

71
00:03:58.738 --> 00:04:00.007
You just made all that up.

72
00:04:00.031 --> 00:04:01.259
I'll send you some podcasts.

73
00:04:01.283 --> 00:04:04.637
Please don't. And what do you
do every morning at 4:00 A.M.?

74
00:04:04.661 --> 00:04:06.848
Morning meditation.
followed by a red-light mask.

75
00:04:06.872 --> 00:04:11.018
followed by some journaling. peloton
ride. cold plunge. eastern sun exposure.

76
00:04:11.042 --> 00:04:12.854
I've never felt better.

77
00:04:12.878 --> 00:04:15.815
So. when did you see
Mr. Beardo Baggins over here?

78
00:04:15.839 --> 00:04:18.443
Yeah. so I went out to get my
meal plan. that's when I saw the guy.

79
00:04:18.467 --> 00:04:20.427
He was right next to joelle's house.

80
00:04:23.638 --> 00:04:24.848
Joelle's.

81
00:04:26.183 --> 00:04:32.022
Yeah. Joelle and Eli's house.
Eli and joelle's house. Eli's house.

82
00:04:38.487 --> 00:04:40.882
- She was a beautiful woman.
- Was she?

83
00:04:40.906 --> 00:04:43.283
Paul. were you and
joelle horn baker intimate?

84
00:04:44.576 --> 00:04:45.845
God. Eli!

85
00:04:45.869 --> 00:04:47.638
- Hey. Hey. hey.
- You killed her. you son of a…

86
00:04:47.662 --> 00:04:49.515
Eli! Eli!

87
00:04:49.539 --> 00:04:52.477
He was sleeping with joelle. She
tried to break it off. and he killed her.

88
00:04:52.501 --> 00:04:54.270
Whoa. whoa. whoa.
I broke it off with her.

89
00:04:54.294 --> 00:04:55.813
Hey!

90
00:04:55.837 --> 00:04:59.609
Hey. listen. I am sorry for your loss.
but I'm gonna need you to calm down

91
00:04:59.633 --> 00:05:01.027
before I have to put you under arrest.

92
00:05:01.051 --> 00:05:02.803
- Get him out of here.
- Let's go.

93
00:05:03.512 --> 00:05:04.513
Okay.

94
00:05:06.097 --> 00:05:08.225
The truth. Right now.

95
00:05:08.809 --> 00:05:10.787
- I didn't kill her.
- But you had an affair.

96
00:05:10.811 --> 00:05:12.145
Well. okay. look. I was…

97
00:05:12.646 --> 00:05:15.541
I was over there for a dinner
party like last year. okay?

98
00:05:15.565 --> 00:05:17.376
We're at the table. I'm across from her.

99
00:05:17.400 --> 00:05:19.545
All of a sudden. I feel
her foot on my crotch.

100
00:05:19.569 --> 00:05:22.215
- Paul...
- no. no. it's not as sexy as it sounds.

101
00:05:22.239 --> 00:05:24.717
She was drunk. I mean. she was.
like. really digging around in there

102
00:05:24.741 --> 00:05:27.678
- like she was trying to find her keys.
- Paul. this is serious!

103
00:05:27.702 --> 00:05:30.705
Yeah. I know it's serious!
She was brutally murdered!

104
00:05:32.624 --> 00:05:36.103
We'd hook up when Eli was away
for business. It was very casual...

105
00:05:36.127 --> 00:05:38.296
when's the last time
you two saw each other?

106
00:05:39.130 --> 00:05:43.009
Last night. You mean
before she was killed?

107
00:05:43.635 --> 00:05:47.389
I only went over there to break
things off with her. which I did.

108
00:05:48.515 --> 00:05:51.118
- Then we had breakup sex.
- Great.

109
00:05:51.142 --> 00:05:54.831
So. you're telling me we're gonna
find your DNA inside the victim?

110
00:05:56.857 --> 00:05:58.751
- Probably. yeah.
- Then you ran up to the crime scene

111
00:05:58.775 --> 00:06:01.629
claiming you saw a shadowy.
bearded. faceless man.

112
00:06:01.653 --> 00:06:03.053
You know what you sound like to me?

113
00:06:03.697 --> 00:06:05.824
- The murderer.
- The murderer.

114
00:06:07.367 --> 00:06:08.719
I don't think he's the murderer.

115
00:06:08.743 --> 00:06:11.371
I think he's a stupid. stupid
man. but he's not our guy.

116
00:06:12.581 --> 00:06:15.268
Well. he's the last known
person to see her alive.

117
00:06:15.292 --> 00:06:17.144
And we'll get DNA.

118
00:06:18.461 --> 00:06:20.982
There's something different
about this case. Amanda.

119
00:06:21.006 --> 00:06:25.468
I don't have it all figured out yet.
but this was not a crime of passion.

120
00:06:26.595 --> 00:06:32.076
Killer is patient. cold. detail-oriented.
none of which reads like Paul camp a no.

121
00:06:32.100 --> 00:06:33.202
Will might be right.

122
00:06:33.226 --> 00:06:35.955
Eli horn baker insisted
the nail gun wasn't his.

123
00:06:35.979 --> 00:06:38.916
so I traced the serial
number to a Brent shipley.

124
00:06:38.940 --> 00:06:41.711
- Did you reach out?
- I don't think he'd answer.

125
00:06:41.735 --> 00:06:45.488
Brent shipley was killed
last year in a home invasion.

126
00:06:46.323 --> 00:06:49.492
Same mo too. No fingerprints and
a weapon left at the crime scene.

127
00:06:51.077 --> 00:06:52.370
You both know what that means.

128
00:06:54.497 --> 00:06:55.957
Serial killer.

129
00:07:00.795 --> 00:07:02.005
What's it look like?

130
00:07:02.589 --> 00:07:04.233
Hit-and-run. No witnesses.

131
00:07:04.257 --> 00:07:07.969
A bagel? Are you kidding me?
Softball season right around the corner.

132
00:07:08.511 --> 00:07:09.791
Kinda feels like you don't care.

133
00:07:10.764 --> 00:07:12.098
Everything.

134
00:07:14.392 --> 00:07:17.163
Who thinks this is a hit-and-run?
The car's still here. O'Hara.

135
00:07:17.187 --> 00:07:20.106
Yeah. well. he hit the
guy and then ran on foot.

136
00:07:20.607 --> 00:07:23.652
The car's registered to a Benjamin price.

137
00:07:24.194 --> 00:07:25.514
Well. it should be easy to solve.

138
00:07:31.618 --> 00:07:34.204
You just had to get pregnant
during softball season. Polaski?

139
00:07:34.788 --> 00:07:36.515
Dude. the pregnancy was unplanned.

140
00:07:36.539 --> 00:07:40.478
Yeah. except no one on our team rounds
the bases like you do. Irreplaceable.

141
00:07:40.502 --> 00:07:41.937
Hey. what color's the Vic's hair?

142
00:07:41.961 --> 00:07:43.731
Black.

143
00:07:43.755 --> 00:07:46.275
Well. I got some white hair
here and some blood too.

144
00:07:46.299 --> 00:07:50.470
Yeah. his eyes are swollen
shut. Whole face is swollen.

145
00:07:51.054 --> 00:07:53.074
He's red. but it doesn't
look like road rash.

146
00:07:53.098 --> 00:07:54.909
Can't even tell where this guy got hit.

147
00:07:54.933 --> 00:07:57.578
You know. Heidi Klum was in
Victoria's secret's runway show

148
00:07:57.602 --> 00:07:59.372
five weeks after she gave birth.

149
00:07:59.396 --> 00:08:02.190
Ooh. You just walked
into a propeller. bud.

150
00:08:03.316 --> 00:08:05.944
Don't you ever compare
me to Heidi Klum again.

151
00:08:06.528 --> 00:08:08.528
or any other woman who
snapped back in five weeks.

152
00:08:09.280 --> 00:08:11.258
- I have a gun.
- Understood.

153
00:08:11.282 --> 00:08:12.534
- Okay.
- Got it.

154
00:08:13.326 --> 00:08:14.744
Take a look at his neck.

155
00:08:16.287 --> 00:08:21.394
Yeah. Broken trachea. at least.
Still doesn't explain the puffy eyes.

156
00:08:21.418 --> 00:08:24.689
Pepper spray.

157
00:08:24.713 --> 00:08:26.089
Okay. so…

158
00:08:27.590 --> 00:08:31.469
Dude gets hit with pepper
spray. has an allergic reaction.

159
00:08:32.262 --> 00:08:37.076
stumbles out into the street
and gets hit by a car on the throat.

160
00:08:37.100 --> 00:08:38.577
That's not real.

161
00:08:38.601 --> 00:08:42.331
You're right. Because this is
the driver. His name is Ben price.

162
00:08:42.355 --> 00:08:45.668
He's 35 years old and
not an organ donor.

163
00:08:45.692 --> 00:08:47.962
Our victim was the
driver? Who did he hit?

164
00:08:47.986 --> 00:08:49.839
And where are they?
And why is he dead?

165
00:08:49.863 --> 00:08:52.633
Well. he got a couple of texts
from somebody named Luna.

166
00:08:52.657 --> 00:08:56.846
"What did you hit? Are you okay?
I can't believe you hung up on me."

167
00:08:56.870 --> 00:08:58.663
- Let's find Luna.
- Let's find Luna.

168
00:09:01.041 --> 00:09:03.168
- You don't want that. do you?
- What?

169
00:09:07.297 --> 00:09:09.257
That's definitely daddy's nail gun.

170
00:09:09.841 --> 00:09:12.278
He always joked it was
the first father's day gift

171
00:09:12.302 --> 00:09:14.054
he didn't have to wear on his feet.

172
00:09:15.680 --> 00:09:19.017
Have you ever seen these
people before. Sandra?

173
00:09:21.144 --> 00:09:22.395
I can't say that I have.

174
00:09:24.105 --> 00:09:25.745
What about the day
your dad was murdered?

175
00:09:26.441 --> 00:09:29.736
I know it's painful. but is there
anything that you can share?

176
00:09:30.320 --> 00:09:32.256
My story hasn't changed.

177
00:09:32.280 --> 00:09:33.799
I stopped by to visit daddy.

178
00:09:33.823 --> 00:09:37.553
and I found him laid out
in the living room. dead.

179
00:09:37.577 --> 00:09:39.722
His head was busted open with a bat.

180
00:09:39.746 --> 00:09:42.892
The irony is he hated baseball.

181
00:09:42.916 --> 00:09:46.586
- He didn't own the bat?
- I never saw it before in my life.

182
00:09:50.715 --> 00:09:52.443
You know. I-I came here today

183
00:09:52.467 --> 00:09:54.904
hoping there was some new
information about daddy's killer.

184
00:09:54.928 --> 00:09:57.531
but it looks like I'm back here
playing storyteller for y'all again.

185
00:09:57.555 --> 00:10:00.016
- I know that it's...
- you don't know a damn thing!

186
00:10:01.518 --> 00:10:02.602
Nothing.

187
00:10:04.187 --> 00:10:08.775
You're right. You're right. I do not know
anything about your pain or your loss.

188
00:10:09.651 --> 00:10:12.171
But I do believe that this murder
is connected to another murder.

189
00:10:12.195 --> 00:10:14.965
which means that we have more
information than we did before.

190
00:10:14.989 --> 00:10:16.699
We're gonna catch him.

191
00:10:22.288 --> 00:10:26.668
I don't know how anyone was
able to sneak up on my dad.

192
00:10:27.252 --> 00:10:29.838
He was so cautious. and he
always had his panic button.

193
00:10:30.547 --> 00:10:32.674
He wore that thing
around like a necklace.

194
00:10:34.968 --> 00:10:36.469
I always thought that maybe…

195
00:10:37.178 --> 00:10:38.596
Maybe your dad knew the killer.

196
00:10:39.139 --> 00:10:40.140
Yeah.

197
00:10:53.945 --> 00:10:58.283
Joelle horn baker was killed with a
nail gun that belonged to Brent shipley.

198
00:10:59.617 --> 00:11:02.912
Brent shipley was murdered
with a bat that wasn't his own.

199
00:11:03.454 --> 00:11:06.332
Maybe it belonged to a previous
victim we don't know about yet.

200
00:11:08.710 --> 00:11:09.919
Maybe it's a pattern.

201
00:11:51.669 --> 00:11:53.606
He's been dead for almost a year now.

202
00:11:53.630 --> 00:11:56.734
Still you might have some
consideration for your husband's memory.

203
00:11:56.758 --> 00:11:59.219
I don't see what Edwin's
got to do with this.

204
00:12:00.011 --> 00:12:02.555
I'm not leaving him. I'm leaving you.

205
00:12:04.224 --> 00:12:06.851
After all we've tried to do for you…

206
00:12:09.312 --> 00:12:12.917
You've both been so very
kind to me. but I'm not really…

207
00:12:12.941 --> 00:12:16.545
So he takes something from each
victim and murders the next guy with it.

208
00:12:16.569 --> 00:12:20.716
It's cute. Little gimmicky. but
whatever. It's not a competition.

209
00:12:20.740 --> 00:12:24.077
Will. will. will. will. will. will. I must say.

210
00:12:24.702 --> 00:12:27.455
you needing me to be the dark you…

211
00:12:29.499 --> 00:12:32.418
Is truly flattering. You must miss me.

212
00:12:33.419 --> 00:12:35.064
How's hell treating you. James?

213
00:12:35.088 --> 00:12:37.173
Too many group activities. Not a fan.

214
00:12:37.674 --> 00:12:39.235
You're going deep with
these "will-o-visions."

215
00:12:39.259 --> 00:12:40.927
adding role-play. I like it.

216
00:12:42.303 --> 00:12:44.138
Trying to get inside the killer's head.

217
00:12:44.681 --> 00:12:50.353
Sure. Whatever you need to
tell yourself. Go ahead. Batter up.

218
00:12:59.070 --> 00:13:01.781
Nice work. What did we learn?

219
00:13:02.865 --> 00:13:04.385
The killer enjoyed it.

220
00:13:04.409 --> 00:13:08.180
Yeah. you did. I love seeing
this side of you. by the way.

221
00:13:08.204 --> 00:13:11.809
Imagine if I were alive. we
could rent a Van with no windows.

222
00:13:11.833 --> 00:13:13.626
We'd have so much fun.

223
00:13:30.351 --> 00:13:31.436
Can I do this one?

224
00:13:32.186 --> 00:13:33.247
No.

225
00:13:33.271 --> 00:13:35.773
Look. she's got a lot of energy.
You might need an extra hand.

226
00:13:40.737 --> 00:13:43.531
No. please.

227
00:13:50.705 --> 00:13:51.706
Why did you stop?

228
00:13:52.248 --> 00:13:54.292
Someone must have blocked her path.

229
00:13:54.834 --> 00:13:58.105
But if someone blocked
poor joelle from escaping.

230
00:13:58.129 --> 00:13:59.464
that must mean…

231
00:14:00.339 --> 00:14:02.276
There's two killers.

232
00:14:02.300 --> 00:14:05.344
It's such a joy to watch you work again.

233
00:14:10.016 --> 00:14:12.828
So. Luna. can you tell us
anything about what was happening

234
00:14:12.852 --> 00:14:14.937
leading up to Benjamin's death?

235
00:14:15.521 --> 00:14:16.773
You know. Ben was my man.

236
00:14:17.732 --> 00:14:20.234
My man. my man. my man.

237
00:14:21.277 --> 00:14:22.695
- I'll show you later.
- Okay.

238
00:14:23.362 --> 00:14:26.717
Were you talking to
Ben right before he died?

239
00:14:26.741 --> 00:14:31.245
We had lunch at r. Thomas grill
and were face timing after we left.

240
