00:28:57.277 --> 00:28:58.445
Why can't I go with you?

481
00:28:59.947 --> 00:29:01.841
Because you are a civilian.

482
00:29:01.865 --> 00:29:03.951
I'm just getting records
of delivery schedules.

483
00:29:08.163 --> 00:29:09.957
Sorry. I don't have a
bowl of water for you.

484
00:29:10.499 --> 00:29:12.417
That's-that's really insulting.

485
00:29:13.001 --> 00:29:16.564
Don't get out. don't talk to
anyone. and don't touch anything.

486
00:29:43.865 --> 00:29:48.829
Special agent will Trent at the gbi. Is
there a manager around I can talk to?

487
00:29:51.164 --> 00:29:54.042
Not a one. special agent
Trent. but what can I do for you?

488
00:29:58.171 --> 00:30:00.507
Special agent Paul camp a no.

489
00:30:01.008 --> 00:30:02.402
Doesn't sound half bad.

490
00:30:02.426 --> 00:30:04.862
I need delivery route
info from the last two years

491
00:30:04.886 --> 00:30:08.366
along with corresponding driver
employee records. Can you do that?

492
00:30:08.390 --> 00:30:10.952
Well. that-that is definitely gonna
be a request for a manager. …

493
00:30:10.976 --> 00:30:13.705
let me see what I can dig up on
the computer. You mind waiting here?

494
00:30:13.729 --> 00:30:14.938
- No problem.
- Cool.

495
00:30:21.278 --> 00:30:23.113
Hey. Mr. Anson.

496
00:30:24.614 --> 00:30:25.907
Your neck's bleeding.

497
00:30:28.535 --> 00:30:30.579
Thanks.

498
00:30:37.085 --> 00:30:40.648
Eduardo. do an image search
for Blair an son in Georgia.

499
00:30:40.672 --> 00:30:41.673
Searching.

500
00:30:54.936 --> 00:30:57.248
The third bullet was found
near the Paul camp a no shooting.

501
00:30:57.272 --> 00:30:59.000
Someone found it in their mailbox.

502
00:30:59.024 --> 00:31:02.253
The bullet was a .38. not the
9mm reported in the summary.

503
00:31:02.277 --> 00:31:04.422
A crime scene specialist
would know the difference.

504
00:31:04.446 --> 00:31:07.550
You think a gbi crime scene
specialist falsified evidence?

505
00:31:07.574 --> 00:31:09.159
Travis Nash. He was at the scene.

506
00:31:10.035 --> 00:31:12.079
Amanda. It's him.

507
00:31:17.209 --> 00:31:18.502
Yeah. there it is.

508
00:31:19.419 --> 00:31:20.837
Paul camp a no.

509
00:31:22.547 --> 00:31:25.568
- How you doing?
- Hey. guy. You were at the…

510
00:31:25.592 --> 00:31:29.197
- The crime scene yesterday. right?
- Yeah. Yeah.

511
00:31:30.931 --> 00:31:32.933
Now. how about we go
inside and see your friend?

512
00:31:35.060 --> 00:31:38.146
- Hey. Gbi. Get to the exit.
- Yes. sir.

513
00:32:06.424 --> 00:32:10.470
Blair an son. I know
about you and your partner.

514
00:32:11.429 --> 00:32:13.616
You guys thought you
made a great team?

515
00:32:13.640 --> 00:32:16.494
You knew how to get into homes.
he knew how to clean up murders.

516
00:32:16.518 --> 00:32:18.562
Nobody can ignore you now. right?

517
00:32:24.276 --> 00:32:27.130
Did you figure me out
too. special agent Trent?

518
00:32:27.154 --> 00:32:28.405
Paul. are you okay?

519
00:32:28.989 --> 00:32:32.409
Sure. yeah. Besides having this gun to
my head. everything's peaches and gravy.

520
00:32:32.909 --> 00:32:35.203
You don't know how long
I've been waiting for this.

521
00:32:43.920 --> 00:32:45.589
Get off!

522
00:33:05.192 --> 00:33:06.836
Everyone thinks you're such a hotshot.

523
00:33:06.860 --> 00:33:08.921
I do all the work. You get all the credit.

524
00:33:08.945 --> 00:33:11.781
Make this easy on
yourself. Put down the knife.

525
00:33:14.701 --> 00:33:15.928
You're always giving orders.

526
00:33:15.952 --> 00:33:18.472
But you're not the one in
charge here. special agent Trent.

527
00:33:26.838 --> 00:33:28.048
So what?

528
00:33:28.965 --> 00:33:30.133
You feel overlooked?

529
00:33:30.675 --> 00:33:33.446
You think that gives you a
reason to kill people in cold blood?

530
00:33:33.470 --> 00:33:34.471
Yeah.

531
00:33:35.555 --> 00:33:36.616
It does.

532
00:34:02.332 --> 00:34:03.375
Do it. you freak.

533
00:34:06.378 --> 00:34:07.605
Do it!

534
00:34:15.095 --> 00:34:16.304
Is it over?

535
00:34:18.807 --> 00:34:22.435
Yeah. it's over.

536
00:34:25.689 --> 00:34:28.084
Thank you so much for
coming back in. Luna. We just…

537
00:34:28.108 --> 00:34:30.461
We have one quick follow-up question.

538
00:34:30.485 --> 00:34:34.799
You said you were on the phone
with Ben when he hit something

539
00:34:34.823 --> 00:34:37.134
- and that cracked the windshield.
- Yeah.

540
00:34:37.158 --> 00:34:38.386
But that's not what happened.

541
00:34:38.410 --> 00:34:40.221
What? Yes. it is.

542
00:34:40.245 --> 00:34:42.723
We talked to the. skunk mother.

543
00:34:42.747 --> 00:34:43.891
The who?

544
00:34:43.915 --> 00:34:47.687
Your boyfriend hit a skunk that belonged
to a woman called the skunk mother.

545
00:34:47.711 --> 00:34:51.607
She got mad. threw a rock at the
car right as he was getting out of it.

546
00:34:51.631 --> 00:34:53.859
She threw a rock. So what?

547
00:34:53.883 --> 00:34:56.237
So how did you know the
windshield was cracked?

548
00:34:56.261 --> 00:34:59.490
You said Ben hung up the
phone before he got out of the car.

549
00:34:59.514 --> 00:35:02.243
She didn't throw the rock
and break the windshield

550
00:35:02.267 --> 00:35:03.744
until he was getting out of the car.

551
00:35:03.768 --> 00:35:05.562
So how did you know about it?

552
00:35:06.313 --> 00:35:08.231
I figured that's what happened.

553
00:35:08.898 --> 00:35:12.027
Guess you figured so much you
drove yourself to the crime scene?

554
00:35:12.652 --> 00:35:14.714
What? What are you saying?

555
00:35:14.738 --> 00:35:16.799
You think I had something
to do with Ben dying?

556
00:35:16.823 --> 00:35:18.759
We pinged your phone
to the nearest tower

557
00:35:18.783 --> 00:35:20.970
and saw that you were in
the area of the crime scene

558
00:35:20.994 --> 00:35:22.096
at the time of the murder.

559
00:35:22.120 --> 00:35:25.874
and witnesses at r. Thomas
grill say you threatened to kill him.

560
00:35:26.416 --> 00:35:28.352
Couples say crazy
things when they're mad.

561
00:35:28.376 --> 00:35:31.129
Yeah. Here's what I think happened.

562
00:35:31.630 --> 00:35:33.983
I think you followed him
while you were on the phone.

563
00:35:34.007 --> 00:35:37.653
and you pulled over when you saw
his car stopped in the middle of the road.

564
00:35:37.677 --> 00:35:40.531
Imagine your surprise
to see Ben on the ground

565
00:35:40.555 --> 00:35:42.783
having an allergic
reaction to pepper spray.

566
00:35:42.807 --> 00:35:45.036
You could have saved him.

567
00:35:45.060 --> 00:35:49.040
Instead. you walked over
there and stomped on his throat.

568
00:35:49.064 --> 00:35:50.440
Was he cheating. Luna?

569
00:35:51.358 --> 00:35:53.544
Did your man. your man.
your man wanna call things off?

570
00:35:53.568 --> 00:35:55.320
What made you so mad?

571
00:35:56.863 --> 00:36:00.116
I supported that bastard
through the pandemic.

572
00:36:02.077 --> 00:36:04.513
He would've been on the
street if it weren't for me.

573
00:36:04.537 --> 00:36:06.223
He just starts making a little bit of money.

574
00:36:06.247 --> 00:36:09.876
and then he wants to leave me
for a stripper at Clermont lounge.

575
00:36:10.669 --> 00:36:12.671
He got off easy.

576
00:36:20.178 --> 00:36:21.489
What's the matter with you guys?

577
00:36:21.513 --> 00:36:24.867
We caught the killer. We
exonerated the skunk mother.

578
00:36:24.891 --> 00:36:25.993
All's right with the world.

579
00:36:26.017 --> 00:36:28.496
- We still need a shortstop. Polaski.
- It's over.

580
00:36:28.520 --> 00:36:31.332
We looked everywhere.
There's nothing we can do.

581
00:36:32.607 --> 00:36:34.794
Maybe we can settle
for a skunky mascot.

582
00:36:34.818 --> 00:36:37.171
Daphne. Hi. What are you doing here?

583
00:36:37.195 --> 00:36:40.591
I'm dropping off some thank-you
cookies for not charging me with murder.

584
00:36:40.615 --> 00:36:42.385
'Cause you didn't murder him.

585
00:36:42.409 --> 00:36:43.678
Take the win. Polaski.

586
00:36:43.702 --> 00:36:46.329
They're black and white.
of course. 'cause the…

587
00:36:46.996 --> 00:36:49.975
And you'll be happy to know that
pernie is on the road to recovery.

588
00:36:49.999 --> 00:36:52.228
Good. This is pernie here?

589
00:36:52.252 --> 00:36:54.021
No. this is crusemire.

590
00:36:54.045 --> 00:36:55.439
Say hello. baby.

591
00:36:55.463 --> 00:36:56.732
- Hey. crusemire.
- Hi.

592
00:36:57.841 --> 00:36:59.527
- Okay.
- Crusemire!

593
00:36:59.551 --> 00:37:01.195
- No. Okay.
- No.

594
00:37:01.219 --> 00:37:02.947
- See if he went that way. all right?
- What is that?

595
00:37:02.971 --> 00:37:04.657
It's okay. He can't spray you.

596
00:37:04.681 --> 00:37:07.576
Actually. he hasn't had
his anal glands removed yet.

597
00:37:07.600 --> 00:37:10.371
You mean to tell me you brought
a loaded skunk into the apd?

598
00:37:10.395 --> 00:37:11.521
That's how people get hurt.

599
00:37:13.273 --> 00:37:14.333
Shh!

600
00:37:14.357 --> 00:37:16.502
No sudden moves. No loud noises.

601
00:37:16.526 --> 00:37:19.964
There is a skunk. it's loose.
and it has its anal glands.

602
00:37:19.988 --> 00:37:22.198
Crusemire.

603
00:37:23.408 --> 00:37:25.052
How do we know if it's gonna spray?

604
00:37:25.076 --> 00:37:28.431
We're fine unless he
starts fluffing his tail.

605
00:37:28.455 --> 00:37:30.683
And he's fluffing.

606
00:37:39.716 --> 00:37:40.884
- Whoa.
- Whoa.

607
00:37:43.470 --> 00:37:44.763
Nice slide.

608
00:37:46.222 --> 00:37:47.223
What's your name?

609
00:37:47.849 --> 00:37:50.202
Officer Sam atkins. sir.

610
00:37:50.226 --> 00:37:51.579
You fresh out of the academy. Sam?

611
00:37:51.603 --> 00:37:52.705
First week here.

612
00:37:52.729 --> 00:37:54.498
Well. congratulations.

613
00:37:54.522 --> 00:37:57.960
You're the new shortstop for the apd
softball team. You played ball before?

614
00:37:57.984 --> 00:37:59.295
I played for Atlanta tech.

615
00:37:59.319 --> 00:38:03.406
I was actually recruited to a double-a
team. but I had a higher purpose.

616
00:38:03.990 --> 00:38:05.718
- Yes. you do.
- Yes. you do.

617
00:38:05.742 --> 00:38:09.472
Hey. team loves hazing rookies.
so this is on you to handle. Sammy.

618
00:38:09.496 --> 00:38:10.497
Good luck.

619
00:38:21.382 --> 00:38:22.467
Heading home?

620
00:38:23.009 --> 00:38:25.571
Yeah. early tee time at the club.

621
00:38:25.595 --> 00:38:27.764
I am back. baby.

622
00:38:28.556 --> 00:38:31.535
Hey. random thought. you ever figure
out how those two guys knew each other?

623
00:38:31.559 --> 00:38:33.394
Friends since elementary school.

624
00:38:33.937 --> 00:38:35.998
Tormented in arms. apparently.

625
00:38:36.022 --> 00:38:39.126
Well. I guess we shouldn't
be so hard on ourselves?

626
00:38:40.652 --> 00:38:43.964
Betty. I'm not taking you
home. Get out of there.

627
00:38:43.988 --> 00:38:45.549
Why is your dog so hot for me?

628
00:38:45.573 --> 00:38:47.200
I don't know.

629
00:38:52.121 --> 00:38:53.748
Hey. Paul.

630
00:38:55.166 --> 00:38:56.459
What did you mean

631
00:38:57.669 --> 00:38:59.170
when you said I started it?

632
00:39:02.048 --> 00:39:04.008
You really don't remember. do you?

633
00:39:08.179 --> 00:39:09.782
You beat me up first.

634
00:39:09.806 --> 00:39:11.909
What? No. I did not.

635
00:39:11.933 --> 00:39:13.601
Why would I make that up?

636
00:39:14.227 --> 00:39:16.914
When I first got to the
home. I was so scared.

637
00:39:16.938 --> 00:39:19.834
I-I didn't know anybody.
all the toys were broken.

638
00:39:19.858 --> 00:39:21.544
And you came back right after me.

639
00:39:21.568 --> 00:39:24.588
You got kicked out of a foster
home or something. right?

640
00:39:26.614 --> 00:39:28.217
Sleeveless Jack.

641
00:39:28.241 --> 00:39:30.869
I will shoot everyone in this house!

642
00:39:31.578 --> 00:39:35.015
No! Jack! No!

643
00:39:35.039 --> 00:39:36.725
I'm so sorry.

644
00:39:37.834 --> 00:39:39.770
Well. I remember picking up a toy gun

645
00:39:39.794 --> 00:39:42.589
and asking you if you wanted
to play cops and robbers.

646
00:39:43.214 --> 00:39:45.192
I pointed the gun at you. and you just…

647
00:39:45.216 --> 00:39:48.654
I mean. for whatever
reason. you just snapped.

648
00:39:48.678 --> 00:39:50.305
I tackled you.

649
00:39:52.599 --> 00:39:53.683
I beat you up.

650
00:39:59.355 --> 00:40:00.875
Why couldn't I remember?

651
00:40:00.899 --> 00:40:02.734
And you had this look in your eye.

652
00:40:03.568 --> 00:40:06.529
I didn't even remember that part
until you came at me this morning.

653
00:40:07.113 --> 00:40:08.156
It was the same look.

654
00:40:09.240 --> 00:40:13.137
Yeah. well. you got me back for years.

655
00:40:13.161 --> 00:40:16.307
Yeah. well. the best
defense is a good offense.

656
00:40:16.331 --> 00:40:18.082
Couldn't let you have the upper hand.

657
00:40:19.959 --> 00:40:22.670
A year ago. I'd flat out
deny this ever happened.

658
00:40:27.508 --> 00:40:28.801
But now I can't.

659
00:40:31.554 --> 00:40:36.893
I'm trying so hard to
stay on the right path.

660
00:40:40.355 --> 00:40:42.899
Not letting my past control my future.

661
00:40:46.027 --> 00:40:48.279
You know. maybe I'm just lying to myself.

662
00:40:48.988 --> 00:40:50.031
You're not lying.

663
00:40:50.907 --> 00:40:52.158
These killers…

664
00:40:53.201 --> 00:40:55.286
I don't know. It's like I understood them.

665
00:40:57.455 --> 00:40:58.623
The fear.

666
00:40:59.707 --> 00:41:00.708
The rage.

667
00:41:03.127 --> 00:41:04.545
I feel those same things.

668
00:41:06.214 --> 00:41:10.819
Anybody who's been through what
we've been through has a monster inside.

669
00:41:12.470 --> 00:41:17.284
But you've turned it
towards something good.

670
00:41:17.308 --> 00:41:19.370
That's why you're different.
You're better than them.

671
00:41:19.394 --> 00:41:20.561
It's the same.

672
00:41:21.813 --> 00:41:25.400
Power over people.
Control over a situation.

673
00:41:28.778 --> 00:41:31.614
I felt way too comfortable
inside their mind.

674
00:41:34.575 --> 00:41:36.244
I nearly killed Nash.

675
00:41:38.579 --> 00:41:40.289
I didn't have to. but…

676
00:41:45.253 --> 00:41:46.504
I wanted to.

677
00:41:51.175 --> 00:41:54.345
You can't let it win. will. You can't.

678
00:41:55.513 --> 00:42:01.704
Every day. I try to get out of my own way.
so I can do whatever it is I'm here to do.

679
00:42:01.728 --> 00:42:04.522
You know? And some
days I win. some days I lose.

680
00:42:05.690 --> 00:42:09.527
Some days I bang my neighbor. and
some days I can't even get out of bed.

681
00:42:10.528 --> 00:42:11.904
but I keep fighting.

682
00:42:13.614 --> 00:42:15.199
You gotta keep fighting too.
